Configure system environment variables: JAVA_HOME and path (done)
Install Node.js and NPM (done)
Go to the root directory of the project for which you want to use Allure Report. Run this command:
{npm install --save-dev allure-commandline}(done but reused)
execute {mvn verify} to run your test(done but reused)
execute {npx allure-commandline serve} to open the report (done but reused)
press ctrl+c to close the temp server once you're done (done but reused)
execute {npx allure-commandline generate --single-file allure-results} to generate a single html file for your allure report done but reused)

